The paper proposes a new data structure for range search on multidimensional points, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and databases. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper mentions fast updation, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence, so it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
